HEADWORD: Semiweekly
<hw>Sem`i*week"ly</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Coming, or made,
or done, once every half week; <as>as, a <ex>semiweekly</ex> newspaper;
a <ex>semiweekly</ex> trip.</as></def> -- <def2><pos>n.</pos> <def>That
which comes or happens once every half week, esp. a semiweekly
periodical.</def></def2> -- <def2><pos>adv.</pos> <def>At intervals of
half a week each.</def></def2>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Semolella</ent>⟦br⟧
